						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">sebanonis wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">But in doing so, I still get the two images, albeit they are both distorted. What am I doing wrong?.</div><br /><br />Okay, I should've asked earlier. What exactly are you wanting on screen? Just one 128x128 display in the center of the screen?<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">sebanonis wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">As for the attribute, am I right in concluding I don't need to do the loop?<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">;&nbsp; &nbsp;ldy&nbsp; &nbsp;#$02&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;; No need to do a loop&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />; DrawAtt:&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;; No need to do a loop<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;lda&nbsp; &nbsp;#$00<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta&nbsp; &nbsp;$2007<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta&nbsp; &nbsp;$2007<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta&nbsp; &nbsp;$2007<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta&nbsp; &nbsp;$2007<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta&nbsp; &nbsp;$2007<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta&nbsp; &nbsp;$2007<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta&nbsp; &nbsp;$2007<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta&nbsp; &nbsp;$2007<br />&nbsp; ; dey&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ; No need to do a loop&nbsp; <br />&nbsp; ; bne&nbsp; &nbsp;DrawAtt&nbsp; &nbsp; ; No need to do a loop<br /></div></div>
<br />
<br />Actually, I was trying to say that in general, you don't NEED a loop to store information to the background. I wasn't referring to your code. But you'll want to do the loop in your case.
<br />
<br />If I were you, I'd scrap the whole mishmash of code, and right a demo from scratch. That way, you should know what's going on. But explain what you want to happen please.</div>

					
